### 📝 Key Points
• S3 is object-based storage.  
• Data is stored inside Buckets.  
• Each file stored is called an Object.  
• S3 supports different storage classes (Standard, IA, Glacier).  
• Versioning helps protect from accidental deletion.  
• By default, S3 buckets are private.
 
